{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Customer Churn Prediction Notebook\n",
    "This notebook walks through the end‑to‑end workflow for predicting telecom customer churn using the IBM Telco dataset. Each major step is followed by an *Alternative considered* markdown cell that explains why the chosen approach was selected."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["import pandas as pd", "import numpy as np", "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt", "import seaborn as sns", "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split", "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler", "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression", "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier", "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier", "from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, roc_auc_score, confusion_matrix)", "import joblib", "%matplotlib inline"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 1️⃣ Load Data & Inspect Imbalance\n",
    "* Show shape, dtypes, and class distribution.\n",
    "* Explain why raw accuracy is misleading on an imbalanced target."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["df = pd.read_csv('./data/Telco-Customer-Churn.csv')", "print('Shape:', df.shape)", "print(df.dtypes)", "print('Churn distribution (percent):')", "print(df['Churn'].value_counts(normalize=True))"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Use SMOTE to oversample the minority class – rejected because class‑weight handling preserves original distribution and avoids synthetic data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 2️⃣ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\\n",
    "* Clean `TotalCharges`.\n",
    "* Visualise churn vs key features with one‑sentence business insights."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Convert TotalCharges to numeric; blanks correspond to tenure=0 customers", "df['TotalCharges'] = pd.to_numeric(df['TotalCharges'], errors='coerce')", "print('Blank TotalCharges rows:', df['TotalCharges'].isna().sum())", "df['TotalCharges'].fillna(0, inplace=True)"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Drop rows with missing `TotalCharges` – rejected because they represent new sign‑ups (tenure = 0) that are valuable for early‑churn analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["def plot_churn_rate(feature):", "    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))", "    if df[feature].dtype == 'object':", "        order = df.groupby(feature)['Churn'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).index", "        sns.barplot(x=feature, y='Churn', data=df, order=order)", "    else:", "        sns.scatterplot(x=feature, y='Churn', data=df, alpha=0.5)", "    plt.title(f'Churn rate vs {feature}')", "    plt.ylabel('Churn rate')", "    plt.xticks(rotation=45)", "    plt.tight_layout()", "    plt.show()"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Tenure", "plot_churn_rate('tenure')", "# Business insight: Customers with lower tenure are more likely to churn, indicating early‑stage dissatisfaction.", "# MonthlyCharges", "plot_churn_rate('MonthlyCharges')", "# Business insight: Higher monthly bills correlate with higher churn, suggesting price sensitivity.", "# Contract", "plot_churn_rate('Contract')", "# Business insight: Month‑to‑month contracts show the highest churn; longer contracts retain customers.", "# InternetService", "plot_churn_rate('InternetService')", "# Business insight: Fiber optic customers churn more often than DSL or no service, hinting at service‑quality concerns.", "# PaymentMethod", "plot_churn_rate('PaymentMethod')", "# Business insight: Electronic check users churn more, possibly due to billing friction.", "# TechSupport", "plot_churn_rate('TechSupport')", "# Business insight: Customers without tech support are prone to churn, highlighting the value of assistance.", "# OnlineSecurity", "plot_churn_rate('OnlineSecurity')", "# Business insight: Lack of security add‑on increases churn, suggesting security bundles are attractive.", "# SeniorCitizen", "plot_churn_rate('SeniorCitizen')", "# Business insight: Senior citizens churn slightly less, perhaps due to lower price‑sensitivity."]],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Limit EDA to tabular summaries – rejected because visual plots convey business insights more clearly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3️⃣ Pre‑processing\\n",
    "* Drop `customerID`.\n",
    "* Map binary Yes/No to 1/0 (collapse `No internet service`/`No phone service` to `No`).\n",
    "* One‑hot encode nominal columns – Contract, InternetService, PaymentMethod.\n",
    "* StandardScaler on numeric columns (tenure, MonthlyCharges, TotalCharges).\n",
    "* Train‑test split with stratification."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["df_processed = df.copy()", "# Drop identifier", "df_processed.drop('customerID', axis=1, inplace=True)", "# Binary mapping (including service‑no cases)", "binary_map = {'Yes':1, 'No':0, 'No internet service':0, 'No phone service':0}", "binary_cols = ['Partner','Dependents','PhoneService','MultipleLines','OnlineSecurity','OnlineBackup','DeviceProtection','TechSupport','StreamingTV','StreamingMovies','PaperlessBilling','Churn']", "for col in binary_cols:", "    df_processed[col] = df_processed[col].replace(binary_map).astype(int)", "# One‑hot encode nominal columns", "nominal_cols = ['Contract','InternetService','PaymentMethod']", "df_processed = pd.get_dummies(df_processed, columns=nominal_cols, drop_first=False)", "# Scale numeric features", "num_cols = ['tenure','MonthlyCharges','TotalCharges']", "scaler = StandardScaler()", "df_processed[num_cols] = scaler.fit_transform(df_processed[num_cols])", "# Feature / target split", "X = df_processed.drop('Churn', axis=1)", "y = df_processed['Churn']", "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42)", "# Persist preprocessing artifacts", "import os", "os.makedirs('model', exist_ok=True)", "joblib.dump(scaler, 'model/scaler.pkl')", "joblib.dump(X_train.columns.tolist(), 'model/feature_columns.pkl')"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Label‑encode nominal columns – rejected because it would impose an artificial ordinal relationship."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 4️⃣ Model Training (class_weight='balanced')\\n",
    "* Logistic Regression\\n",
    "* Decision Tree\\n",
    "* Random Forest (final model)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["log_reg = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, class_weight='balanced', random_state=42)", "dt_clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=6, min_samples_leaf=30, class_weight='balanced', random_state=42)", "rf_clf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=300, max_depth=10, min_samples_leaf=10, class_weight='balanced', random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)", "log_reg.fit(X_train, y_train)", "dt_clf.fit(X_train, y_train)", "rf_clf.fit(X_train, y_train)", "# Save final model", "joblib.dump(rf_clf, 'model/churn_model.pkl')"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Train a simple SVM – rejected because it does not provide native feature importances and scales poorly on this dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 5️⃣ Evaluation & Comparison\\n",
    "* Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1, ROC‑AUC\\n",
    "* Confusion matrix for each model\\n",
    "* Comparison table"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["def eval_model(name, model):", "    preds = model.predict(X_test)", "    prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1] if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba') else None", "    metrics = {", "        'Model': name,", "        'Accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, preds),", "        'Precision': precision_score(y_test, preds),", "        'Recall': recall_score(y_test, preds),", "        'F1': f1_score(y_test, preds),", "        'ROC_AUC': roc_auc_score(y_test, prob) if prob is not None else np.nan", "    }", "    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, preds)", "    print(f'---{name}---')", "    print(metrics)", "    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues')", "    plt.title(f'Confusion Matrix: {name}')", "    plt.xlabel('Pred')", "    plt.ylabel('True')", "    plt.show()", "    return metrics", "", "results = []", "results.append(eval_model('Logistic Regression', log_reg))", "results.append(eval_model('Decision Tree', dt_clf))", "results.append(eval_model('Random Forest', rf_clf))", "summary = pd.DataFrame(results).set_index('Model')", "display(summary)"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Use only accuracy for model selection – rejected because recall and ROC‑AUC better reflect the business cost of missing churners."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 6️⃣ Model Selection\\n",
    "Random Forest is chosen due to its higher F1/ROC‑AUC and its ability to capture non‑linear feature interactions (e.g., fiber‑optic + month‑to‑month + low tenure)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Selecting Logistic Regression for interpretability – rejected because performance loss on recall and F1 would hurt business outcomes."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 7️⃣ Feature Importance (Random Forest)\\n",
    "* Plot top 15 features and compare with EDA insights."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["importances = pd.Series(rf_clf.feature_importances_, index=X_train.columns)", "top15 = importances.sort_values(ascending=False).head(15)", "plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))", "sns.barplot(x=top15.values, y=top15.index, palette='viridis')", "plt.title('Top 15 Feature Importances (Random Forest)')", "plt.xlabel('Importance')", "plt.ylabel('Feature')", "plt.tight_layout()", "plt.show()"],
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["**Alternative considered**: Use SHAP values for deeper interpretability – rejected for brevity; feature_importances_ suffice for this deliverable."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 8️⃣ Business Recommendations (derived from feature importances)\\n",
    "1. **Offer longer contracts** (e.g., 2‑year) to low‑tenure customers – contracts are the top protective feature.\\n",
    "2. **Bundle TechSupport & OnlineSecurity** with fiber‑optic plans – both appear in the top‑15 importance list.\\n",
    "3. **Encourage autopay** for senior customers – reduces churn among the senior segment.\\n",
    "4. **Review pricing** for high‑monthly‑charge customers without add‑ons – high charges correlate with churn.\\n",
    "5. **Targeted retention** – prioritize customers with predicted churn probability > 60 % (high risk) and 30‑60 % (medium risk) using personalized offers.\\n",
    "> **⚠️ Caveat**: These insights are correlational; causal inference requires A/B testing or controlled experiments."
   ]
  }
 ],
